Package: wkpool
Title: Vertex Pool Topology for Well-Known Geometry
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Michael", "Sumner", , "mdsumner@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Establishes and maintains vertex pool topology for geometry 
    handled by 'wk'. Segments are the atomic unit, vertices are shared via
    integer references into a pool. Topology is discoverable (via coincident
    vertex detection) not imposed - representing the truth of the input.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports: 
    vctrs,
    wk
Suggests:
    RTriangle,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
